# Branches and development flow

Full guide: `docs/contributing/branches.md`

## Rules

- **Never commit directly to `main`** — use topic branches + PR
- Trunk-based: short-lived branches merge into `main` only
- Branch naming: `<type>/<short-description>` in English (e.g. `feat/order-idempotency`)
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`, `ci`, `perf`, `hotfix`
- Releases: tag on `main` (`vX.Y.Z`), not a separate release branch
- Keep topic branches synced with `main` via rebase when possible
- Delete topic branch after PR merge

## Standard flow

```
main → checkout -b feat/... → TDD + commits → push → PR to main → CI + review → merge → delete branch
```

## Commit destination

| Work | Branch |
|------|--------|
| Any code/docs change | topic branch → PR → `main` |
| Release | PR bumping VERSION/CHANGELOG on `main` → tag `vX.Y.Z` |
| Hotfix | `hotfix/*` → PR → `main` → patch tag |
